# ReviewBuddy Core Rules for Cursor IDE

## Project Context

**ReviewBuddy** - AI-powered code review GitHub Action (JavaScript, Node.js ≥18.0.0)

## Mandatory Workflows

```bash
npm install          # Install dependencies
npm test            # Run tests
npm run lint        # ESLint check
node src/index.js   # Local testing (requires env vars)
```

## Definition of "Done"

- ✅ Code follows adapter pattern
- ✅ All secrets masked with `core.setSecret()`
- ✅ Input validation implemented
- ✅ Error handling with `core.setFailed()`
- ✅ Rate limiting and retries
- ✅ Tests pass (if exist)
- ✅ README.md updated
- ✅ action.yml updated
- ✅ No hardcoded credentials

## Architecture

```
GitHub PR Event → Parse Inputs → Fetch PR Details → Select AI Adapter → Generate Review → Post Comments → Update PR
```

## Components

```
src/ (index.js, adapters/, prompts/, github/, utils/)
action.yml (GitHub Action metadata)
```

## GitHub Actions Standards

### Inputs/Outputs
```javascript
// ✅ Use @actions/core
const token = core.getInput('github-token', { required: true });
core.setOutput('review-result', result);

// ✅ Use core.setFailed for errors
try {
  await reviewPR();
} catch (error) {
  core.setFailed(error.message);
}
```

### Security
```javascript
// ✅ ALWAYS: Mask secrets
const apiKey = core.getInput('gemini-api-key', { required: true });
core.setSecret(apiKey);

// ❌ NEVER: Log credentials
console.log(`API Key: ${apiKey}`); // FORBIDDEN
```

### Type Safety (JSDoc)
```javascript
/**
 * @param {string} code - Source code to review
 * @param {object} context - GitHub context
 * @returns {Promise<object>} Review result
 */
async function generateReview(code, context) {}
```

## Key Patterns

### Adapter Pattern (AI Providers)
```javascript
class AIAdapter {
  async generateReview(code, context) {
    throw new Error('Not implemented');
  }
}

class GeminiAdapter extends AIAdapter {
  async generateReview(code, context) {
    // Gemini-specific implementation
  }
}

const adapters = {
  gemini: new GeminiAdapter(),
  openrouter: new OpenRouterAdapter(),
  github: new GitHubModelsAdapter()
};
```

### Personas
```javascript
const personas = {
  roast: "Brutally honest, sarcastic",
  professional: "Senior engineer, detailed",
  funny: "Comedian-style, humorous",
  friendly: "Supportive mentor"
};
```

### Error Handling (Exponential Backoff)
```javascript
async function callAI(prompt, retries = 3) {
  for (let i = 0; i < retries; i++) {
    try {
      return await api.generate(prompt);
    } catch (error) {
      if (error.status === 429) {
        await sleep(Math.pow(2, i) * 1000);
        continue;
      }
      throw error;
    }
  }
}
```

## Testing

```javascript
jest.mock('@actions/core');
jest.mock('@actions/github');

test('should generate review', async () => {
  core.getInput.mockReturnValue('gemini');
  const result = await generateReview(mockContext);
  expect(result).toHaveProperty('suggestions');
});
```

## Anti-Patterns

❌ Hardcoded credentials
❌ Synchronous operations (use Promise.all)
❌ No retry logic
❌ Logging secrets

